      • checkDatatypeCompatibility

        public static boolean checkDatatypeCompatibility(IDatatype datatype1,
                                                 IDatatype datatype2,
                                                 boolean partialRecordSupport)
        Checks the compatibility of two datatypes If partialRecordSupport is true, record types are also considered compatible according to section 3.4.1.2.1, rule 3 of the "AUTOSAR Software Component Template", release 3.2, document version 3.4.0 (the requested record type only has to provide a sub set of the provided record type). For this check, datatype1 is considered the required type and datatype2 is considered the provided type.
        Parameters:
        datatype1 - A datatype (the required type, if partial record support is enabled)
        datatype2 - A datatype (the provided type, if partial record support is enabled)
        partialRecordSupport - If partial record support shall be enabled
        Returns:
        True if the datatypes are compatible, false otherwise
